  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_london_borough">London Borough</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_geographic_area">GEOGRAPHIC AREA</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_london_borough">London Boroughs</xref>
 are the local government areas within Greater London. The Borough Councils are unitary administrations with a status similar to 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_metropolitan_district">Metropolitan Districts</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_london_borough">London Boroughs</xref>
, see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_office_for_national_statistics">Office for National Statistics</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/census/2001censusandearlier/glossary/hn"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Glossary</xref>
.  </p>

